<article>
    <topic>
        <title>API References for GacUI</title>
        <topic>
            <title>Resources</title>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/tutorial.html">Tutorial</a>: build your first GacUI application.</li>
                    <li><a href="/download.html">Tutorial</a>: download this library.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                If you don't need runtime reflection on C++ classes,
                it is recommended to add <b>VCZH_DEBUG_NO_REFLECTION</b> to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/build/reference/d-preprocessor-definitions">preprocessor definitions</a>.
                By doing this, unnecessary code are eliminated, which significantly reduces both executable size and object sizes.
            </p>
        </topic>
        <topic>
            <title>Source Files for GacUI</title>
            <topic>
                <title>for typical GacUI applications</title>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>GacUI.h</b> and <b>GacUI.cpp</b></li>
                        <li><b>GacUIWindows.h</b> and <b>GacUIWindows.cpp</b></li>
                        <li><b>DarkSkin.h</b> and <b>DarkSkin.cpp</b></li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    It is highly recommended to use generated C++ code from GacUI XML resource compiled using <b>GacBuild.ps1</b> (see the <li><a href="/tutorial.html">tutorial</a>).
                    By not using reflection, it reduces about 90% of the execution size, which significantly improves the performance.
                </p>
            </topic>
            <topic>
                <title>for loading compiled GacUI XML resource without C++ code generation</title>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>(all source files above)</li>
                        <li><b>GacUIReflection.h</b> and <b>GacUIReflection.cpp</b></li>
                        <li><b>DarkSkinReflection.h</b> and <b>DarkSkinReflection.cpp</b></li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you need to dynamically load UI from other sources,
                    reflection is then needed,
                    because classes for windows and controls is generated using Workflow script,
                    and stores in multiple binary files for different platforms.
                </p>
            </topic>
            <topic>
                <title>for compileing GacUI XML resource at runtime</title>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>(all source files above)</li>
                        <li><b>GacUICompiler.h</b> and <b>GacUICompiler.cpp</b></li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </topic>
        </topic>
